            "description": "I am an active member of the Ariel Science Consortium, in which I contribute to the development of future numerical tools and observation strategies through the chemical modelling of exoplanet atmospheres. More specifically, I am a member of the Chemistry, Retrieval and Phase Curves working groups. Ariel is an ESA space telescope that will be dedicated to observations of exoplanet atmospheres.",
