        {
            "title": "Astronomical observing run Mercator telescope: Differential abundances in exo-planet hosting binary",
            "date": {
                "start": {
                    "month": 10,
                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2016
                },
                "end": {
                    "month": 12,
                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2016
                }
            },
            "description": "As part of my education in Astronomy and Astrophysics at the University of Leuven I have conducted one week of research using the Mercator telescope at La Palma. Together with a small team of students we directly operated the telescope in order to collect data for scientific research done at the University of Leuven, as well as data needed for a research project of my own. In my project I investigate whether there are differences present in the elemental abundances of binary stellar components of which one hosts an exo-planet. During the week of this observing run I closely worked together with my team members: fellow students and researchers. Since it was an international collaboration, all communication was in English.",
